Risks of Stablecoins
	‚Ä¢	Centralization risk
	‚Ä¢	Regulatory bans
	‚Ä¢	Reserve transparency issues
	‚Ä¢	De-pegging risk

Regulation Status (High-Level)
USA   : Regulated, reserve audits
EU      : MiCA regulation
India   : No INR stablecoin allowed yet
Global: Under active regulation
One-Line Exam Answers
Stablecoin: A cryptocurrency designed to maintain price stability by pegging to real-world assets.
First stablecoin: Tether (USDT), 2014.
Main use: Payments, trading, DeFi, remittances.
Final Summary
Stablecoins combine the stability of fiat currency with the speed and programmability of blockchain, making them the backbone of modern crypto finance.

What is the Bitcoin Policy Institute (BPI)?
The Bitcoin Policy Institute is a non-partisan, nonprofit think tank dedicated to studying Bitcoin‚Äôs public policy and societal implications. It focuses on research, education, and engagement with policymakers to help governments, regulators, and the public understand Bitcoin‚Äôs technical and economic properties and how policy should be shaped around it. 
Bitcoin Policy Institute
Key Focus Areas
	‚Ä¢	Future of Money ‚Äì Bitcoin‚Äôs role in monetary systems
	‚Ä¢	National Security & Geopolitics ‚Äì Strategic impacts of Bitcoin
	‚Ä¢	Mining & Energy ‚Äì How Bitcoin mining affects energy systems
	‚Ä¢	Financial Inclusion & Human Rights ‚Äì Access to finance and personal freedom
	‚Ä¢	Research that informs legislation, regulation, and public understanding of Bitcoin. 
When and Where Was It Established?
	‚Ä¢	Founded: 2021
	‚Ä¢	Headquarters: Washington, D.C., United States
	‚Ä¢	Legal Status: Registered as a 501(c)(3) nonprofit organization (U.S. tax-exempt educational charity) 
The institute was launched in 2021 out of a perceived need for rigorous, evidence-based Bitcoin policy research, especially in the context of rapidly evolving global discussions on digital assets and regulation. 
Bitcoin Policy Institute
What Does the Bitcoin Policy Institute Do?
1. Research That Informs Policy
	‚Ä¢	BPI publishes in-depth research on topics such as:
	‚Ä¢	How Bitcoin could influence monetary policy
	‚Ä¢	Energy and mining policy
	‚Ä¢	National security implications
	‚Ä¢	Financial inclusion and civil liberties 
	‚Ä¢	Bitcoin Policy Institute
 2. Education & Outreach
	‚Ä¢	The institute conducts:
	‚Ä¢	Briefings and workshops for lawmakers and staff
	‚Ä¢	A Congressional Fellowship Program
	‚Ä¢	Public educational materials explaining Bitcoin fundamentals in policy terms 
3. Engagement with Policymakers
BPI regularly:
	‚Ä¢	Advises federal agencies and legislative offices
	‚Ä¢	Testifies in hearings
	‚Ä¢	Offers real-time policy analysis during major developments 
4. Bitcoin Policy Summit
	‚Ä¢	BPI hosts a major annual event ‚Äî the Bitcoin Policy Summit ‚Äî bringing together:
	‚Ä¢	Members of U.S. Congress
	‚Ä¢	Federal regulators
	‚Ä¢	Industry leaders
	‚Ä¢	Experts in Bitcoin policy and strategy
	‚Ä¢	The 2025 summit was held on June 25‚Äì26, 2025 in Washington, D.C., showcasing its role as a central forum for Bitcoin policy discussion. 
2025 Bitcoin Policy Summit
Why It Matters
Bitcoin policy debates affect how governments regulate digital assets, protect consumers, approach monetary innovation, and consider the geopolitical and economic roles of decentralized money. BPI works to ensure these decisions are grounded in technical accuracy and economic reality rather than misinformation or hype. 
Bitcoin Policy Institute
Related: Bitcoin Policy Institute of India
Separately, an Indian chapter or initiative called the Bitcoin Policy Institute of India (BPI India) was launched on August 15, 2025 (India‚Äôs Independence Day) with a mission to promote Bitcoin research and policy discussion in India ‚Äî especially around financial sovereignty, sustainable mining, and policy advocacy. This is distinct from the U.S.-based BPI but inspired by similar goals of informed policy engagement. 
One-Sentence Summary
The Bitcoin Policy Institute is a Washington, D.C.-based nonprofit think tank, founded in 2021, that conducts research, education, and policy engagement to help shape sound public policy about Bitcoin in the U.S. and beyond.

